<taxonomicName id="CB8B14B7FFF1A043832CECCEFD81FB17" authority="Bleeker, 1862" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1862" box="[327,633,1185,1209]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Parancistrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="573" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3EFFB326FFF1A043832CECCEFD81FB17" bold="true" box="[327,633,1185,1209]" pageId="2" pageNumber="573">
<emphasis id="3EFFB326FFF1A043832CECCEFE2DFB17" bold="true" box="[327,469,1185,1209]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="573">Parancistrus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="681A12C5FFF1A04383B6ECCDFD81FB17" author="Bleeker, P" box="[477,633,1186,1209]" pageId="2" pageNumber="573" pagination="1 - 112" refId="ref4284" refString="Bleeker, P. 1862. Atlas ichthyologique des Indes orientales neerlandaises, publie sous les auspices du Gouvernment colonial neerlndaises: Siluroides, Chacoides et Heterobranchoides (Fr. Muller, Amsterdam), 2: 1 - 112, pls. 49 - 101." type="journal article" year="1862">Bleeker, 1862</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="44913CBFFFF1A04382F5EC8CFD7BF9D4" pageId="2" pageNumber="573" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0C346F34FFF1A04382F5EC8CFD7BF9D4" blockId="2.[158,801,1251,1658]" pageId="2" pageNumber="573">
<emphasis id="3EFFB326FFF1A04382F5EC8CFEF5FB54" bold="true" box="[158,269,1251,1274]" pageId="2" pageNumber="573">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="CB8B14B7FFF1A0438376EC8BFE50FB55" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1862" box="[285,424,1252,1275]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Parancistrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="573" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3EFFB326FFF1A0438376EC8BFE50FB55" box="[285,424,1252,1275]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="573">Parancistrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be characterized by the presence of a membranous connection between the dorsal and adipose fins, cephalic and body scutes not carinate and a large gill opening. 
<bibRefCitation id="681A12C5FFF1A0438309ED2CFDD2FAF4" author="Armbruster, J" box="[354,554,1347,1370]" pageId="2" pageNumber="573" refId="ref4202" refString="Armbruster, J. W. 1997. Phylogenetic relationships of the suckermouth armoured catfishes (Loricariidae) with particular emphasis on the Ancistrinae, Hypostominae and Neoplecostominae. Unpublished Ph. D. Dissertation, University of Illinois, Urbana-Champaign." type="book" year="1997">Armbruster (1997)</bibRefCitation>
additionally diagnosed the genus based on posterior deflection of the hyomandibula and presence of fleshy folds along the dorsal-fin base of nuptial males. 
<taxonomicName id="CB8B14B7FFF1A043835CEDCBFE39FA15" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1862" box="[311,449,1444,1467]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Parancistrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="573" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3EFFB326FFF1A043835CEDCBFE39FA15" box="[311,449,1444,1467]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="573">Parancistrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be further distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="CB8B14B7FFF1A04382F5EDACFEFCFA74" authorityName="Kner" authorityYear="1854" box="[158,260,1475,1498]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Ancistrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="573" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3EFFB326FFF1A04382F5EDACFEFCFA74" box="[158,260,1475,1498]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="573">Ancistrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CB8B14B7FFF1A043832BEDADFE36FA74" box="[320,462,1474,1498]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Chaetostoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="573" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3EFFB326FFF1A043832BEDADFE36FA74" box="[320,462,1474,1498]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="573">Chaetostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a plated snout and from all other genera of the Ancistrini (sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="681A12C5FFF1A04380F4ED8CFF27F9B4" author="Armbruster, J" pageId="2" pageNumber="573" pagination="1 - 80" refId="ref4244" refString="Armbruster, J. W. 2004. Phylogenetic relationships of the suckermouth armoured catfishes (Loricariidae) with emphasis on the Hypostominae and the Ancistrinae. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 141: 1 - 80." type="journal article" year="2004">Armbruster, 2004</bibRefCitation>
), except 
<taxonomicName id="CB8B14B7FFF1A043830CEE6BFDEBF9B5" box="[359,531,1540,1563]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Baryancistrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="573" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3EFFB326FFF1A043830CEE6BFDEBF9B5" box="[359,531,1540,1563]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="573">Baryancistrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CB8B14B7FFF1A043805AEE6DFD20F9B4" box="[561,728,1538,1562]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Oligancistrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="573" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3EFFB326FFF1A043805AEE6DFD20F9B4" box="[561,728,1538,1562]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="573">Oligancistrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="CB8B14B7FFF1A04382F5EE4DFEA4F994" authorityName="Nijssen &amp; Isbrucker" authorityYear="1987" box="[158,348,1570,1594]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Spectracanthicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="573" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3EFFB326FFF1A04382F5EE4DFEA4F994" box="[158,348,1570,1594]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="573">Spectracanthicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the connection between dorsal and adipose fins; from 
<taxonomicName id="CB8B14B7FFF1A04383E2EE2BFDD6F9F5" box="[393,558,1604,1627]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Baryancistrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="573" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3EFFB326FFF1A04383E2EE2BFDD6F9F5" box="[393,558,1604,1627]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="573">Baryancistrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CB8B14B7FFF1A0438028EE2DFD1CF9F4" box="[579,740,1602,1626]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Oligancistrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="573" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3EFFB326FFF1A0438028EE2DFD1CF9F4" box="[579,740,1602,1626]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="573">Oligancistrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="CB8B14B7FFF1A04382F5EE0DFEA0F9D4" authorityName="Nijssen &amp; Isbrucker" authorityYear="1987" box="[158,344,1634,1658]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Spectracanthicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="573" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3EFFB326FFF1A04382F5EE0DFEA0F9D4" box="[158,344,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="573">Spectracanthicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the large gill openings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
